captions.text: -Hi, guys.

It's Brooklyn and
Bailey, and today, we

decided it'd be super fun to
do a May favorites video, which

is basically a video where
we show you guys some

of our favorite
products from May.

-Like our favorite
food, our favorite hair

stuff, our favorite
clothing items.
-Yeah.

A whole bunch of awesome
stuff, so maybe you guys
can try some of them out.
I don't know.

We're so excited to show
you, so let's get started.

-We're going to start off
with some of our food items.

So this was one of my
favorites from May.
They're the Tropical Starburst.
They're actually kind of new.

I was really excited when they
came out with the all red bag,

because I just love
the reds, but then they

came out with these flavors,
and they're so good.

There's-- I'm trying
to read upside down.

-Cherry Kiwi, Pina Colada, Mango
Melon, and Strawberry Banana.
-They're so good.

They kind of remind
me of summer,

and I've been
really loving these,

so I would definitely
recommend them.

-For my food, I have Annie's
Homegrown Shells and White

Cheddar mac and
cheese, and you get
this from Walmart or Target.
Basically, any store carries it.
And it is so good.

Normally, we eat the Kraft mac
and cheese, the traditional mac

and cheese, but a friend
introduced this to us,

and ever since then, we have
been eating all the time.

-It's so weird
because we usually
just like normal cheese.

We've never really liked
white cheddar cheese before,

and then we tried this,
and it was so good.
-It's so good.

So if you want some yummy mac
and cheese, this is the one.
-Eat Annie's.

-And then for
another food product,

we have been drinking a lot
of this lately, Sonic slushes.

And it's a new discovery,
but you can add Nerds

to your slushes, and it
is just so delicious.

-They have a billion flavors
for slushies, for shakes.

They have everything, but
my favorite flavor is peach.
-And I like green apple.
I like the sour flavors.

But they're so good,
and we just love
adding the Nerds and stuff.

It just creates such
a heavenly flavor.
It's so delicious.

-Now we're going to go on to
some of our favorite makeup
and hygiene products.

I have these two face washes
that I've been loving a lot.

One of them is called the
apricot scrub by St. Ives,

and for some reason, I actually
remember my friend just

leaving it at my house, and
she's like, why don't you
just try this?

So I tried it and I loved
it so I got some for myself.
You can get it at Target.
It's really helpful.
I love it.

It just helps
exfoliate the skin.

And then I have this one,
which is an oil absorbing cream
by Clean and Clear.

And I love this one
because as a teenager,
you're going to have oily skin.

It's completely
normal, but this really

helps reduce it and make
it look a lot fresher.
I love both of these.
-My hygiene product.

I actually have some
Suave deodorant.

It's kind of a weird
product to talk about,

but I absolutely love it
and it smells so good.

-I mean, every person
has to use deodorant.

-This flavor or
smell or whatever--
-Not flavor.

-It's called Tropical
Paradise, and it smells just
like flowers and heaven.
It smells really good.

And I've actually had
people compliment me

on it, which is strange,
considering they probably

shouldn't be able to smell
my deodorant, but they can.

And it smelled really good,
which is I guess a good thing.

So I actually had people
compliment me on it,

so if you want something
that smells really good,

use the Suave 24 Hour
Tropical Paradise deodorant.

-The next make up product I have
is the Organic Wear Physician's
Formula mascara.

We have the green leaf one,
but the silver one just
helps lengthen your eyelashes.
I love this.

You can get it at Target
or at Ulta, wherever,

but we definitely recommend
this as your mascara.

-Next up, we have a Makeup
Forever face powder.

This face powder, you put it
on to set your make up and make
your face look less oily.

It's white and it
goes on translucent,

so it doesn't have to
match any skin tone.
We love using it all the time.

We use it on and off
camera all the time.

You can get this at Sephora,
so if you want to go get some,
go there.

-The next product that I
have is an Essie nail polish
that we just found.

It was at Target, and it's
called Serial Shopper.

It's kind of a salmony pink,
and I'm actually wearing it.

I just love it because it's
bright and happy and fun,

so I would definitely
recommend this nail polish.

-I have a vanilla
buttercream hand lotion,

and I got this from
Bath and Body Works.

I did get this for Easter,
but it's almost gone.
I love the product so much.
-It smells so good.
-It smells so good.

Every time I walk
into class, I'm like,

yeah, I smell so good,
because people just

tell me all the time
that it smells so good,
and I love it so much.

-You and your deodorant
and your vanilla lotion.
You smell so good.
-I do.

And you can get
this at-- I already

told you-- Bath and Body Works,
so if you want to get that.

-Next up, we have my favorite
pair of shoes lately.
Sorry.

I have to read the
company's name.
I can never pronounce it.
Mossimo.
Mossimo.

Anyway, they're a pewter
color, and they're
really, really cute.
They're strappy.

They've got a couple
of studs on them.

They're really cool, great
for spring or summer,

so I would definitely
recommend these.
You can get them at Target.
That's where we found these.

And there's also a black as
well, I think, in the colors.

I would definitely
recommend these sandals.

One of our favorite
TV shows from May

is "Once Upon a Time," which
I know is kind of an old one,

but we just discovered
it and we're loving it.

It's kind of about these
fairytale characters--
-In the real world.
-Yes.

And they're trying to get
back to their fairy tale land.
It's really good.

We love fairy tales
because we read a bunch,
so watching them is even better.

-So if you want to find them,
both of the first seasons

are on Netflix, so
watch that TV show.

Next up, we are going
to talk about music.
We have two favorite artists.
Mine is Ed Sheeran.
-And mine is Jess Penner.

-And I absolutely love
both of these artists.
They have good music.

I think Ed Sheeran's been on
the radio for a little while.
-Yeah.

Jess Penner has peppy,
fun, uplifting music.
I love all of her songs.
-We love it a lot.

We've been listening to
lots of music this month,

and those are our
two favorite artists.

-Thank you guys so much for
watching our May favorites
video.
It was a ton of fun to film.

-Also, don't forget
to leave a comment

below on any new discoveries
you guys have found.
We don't care what it is.

It could be hair products,
hygiene products, food.

We want to hear
about it, so don't
forget to leave a comment below.

-And we just recently
made a new video
based off of "Maleficent."

We did a make up haul
for Disney Style.

And there will be a link
here and a link below

in the description box
if you want to see that,
so click on it.

There will be two videos
from us this week,

this one and the
"Maleficent" one,
so if you want to check it out.

And we'll see you
guys next week.
-Bye.
Bye.
-Like a flaming red.

-We actually have
these on our nails.

-We put them on and
they work really well.
We love them so much.

The colors go on well,
they stay on well.
-They dried fast.
-How normal does that look?

-I'm getting a
face full of hair.
-Pull my hair over my shoulder.

-I'm literally breathing
hair right now.
-How does that look?
Pretty unnatural?
